 or ‘sunbeam’ compare Greek <i>hēlios</i> ‘sun’. It has sometimes been taken as connected with the Greek word meaning ‘Greek’, <i>Hellēn</i>, but this is doubtful. In the early Christian period the name was borne by the mother of the Emperor Constantine, who is now usually known by the Latin version of her name, <i>Helena</i>. She is credited with having found the True Cross in Jerusalem. She was born in about  248 , probably in Bithynia. However, in medieval England it was believed that she had been born in Britain, which greatly increased the popularity of the name there."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":19,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Lady Gladys Helen Meierstein was born about 1240, in England. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir William James O' Conner. She died in 1260, in her hometown, at the age of 21."},"et":{"Abt 1240–1260":"umbes 1240–1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1253–1280":"1253–1280","Abt 1240":"umbes 1240","1259":"1259","1253":"1253","1240":"1240","about 1253":"umbes 1253","1260":"1260","1280":"1280","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"Abt 1240–1260":"noin 1240–1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1253–1280":"1253–1280","Abt 1240":"noin 1240","1259":"1259","1253":"1253","1240":"1240","about 1253":"noin 1253","1260":"1260","1280":"1280","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England","Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"England"},"fr":{"Abt 1240–1260":"environ 1240–1260","1240–1260":"1240–1260","1253–1280":"1253–1280","Abt 1240":"environ 1240","12